abstract class CoinText {
  static const String ETH =
      "Ethereum (ETH) is one of the most well-known and widely used cryptocurrencies, second only to Bitcoin in terms of market capitalization. It was proposed by Vitalik Buterin in late 2013 and development was crowdfunded in 2014, with the network going live on July 30, 2015. Ethereum introduced the concept of smart contracts, which are self-executing contracts with the terms of the agreement directly written into code. This allows for decentralized applications (dApps) to be built on the Ethereum blockchain, enabling a wide range of use cases including decentralized finance (DeFi), non-fungible tokens (NFTs), and decentralized autonomous organizations (DAOs).ETH serves as the native cryptocurrency of the Ethereum platform, used to pay for transaction fees and computational services when interacting with smart contracts and dApps. Ethereum operates on a Proof of Work (PoW) consensus mechanism, although there are plans to transition to a Proof of Stake (PoS) model with the upcoming Ethereum 2.0 upgrade. This upgrade aims to improve scalability, security, and sustainability while reducing energy consumption.Ethereum has a vibrant and active community of developers and users, with a wide range of projects and applications being built on its blockchain. Its flexibility and programmability have contributed to its popularity and widespread adoption within the blockchain and cryptocurrency ecosystem.";
